#!/bin/bash
# Umbra OS — i3 keybinding cheatsheet (opened with Super+Shift+/).
cat <<'EOF'

   UMBRA OS · i3 tiling desktop — keybindings   (Super = Windows key)

   NO SUPER KEY? (common in VirtualBox) — use the TASKBAR at the bottom:
   click "≡ APPS" to launch anything, or the Firefox / Term / Files / Keys
   / Settings / Monitor / Shot buttons. Everything is mouse-clickable.

   Super+Return ....... terminal (alacritty)
   Super+d ............ app launcher (rofi)
   Super+Shift+d ...... run a command
   Super+q ............ close window
   Super+g / n / p .... Firefox / Files / KeePassXC

   Super+h j k l ...... focus left/down/up/right  (or arrows)
   Super+Shift+hjkl ... move window
   Super+1..0 ......... switch workspace
   Super+Shift+1..0 ... send window to workspace

   Super+b / v ........ split horizontal / vertical
   Super+f ............ fullscreen
   Super+w / s / e .... tabbed / stacked / toggle split
   Super+Shift+space .. float toggle
   Super+r ............ resize mode (hjkl, Esc to exit)

   Print .............. screenshot region -> clipboard
   Super+Print ........ screenshot -> ~/umbra-*.png
   Super+Shift+x ...... lock screen
   Super+Shift+e ...... log out
   Super+Shift+r ...... restart i3 (reload)

   opsec:  umbra-verify.sh · umbra-torswitch · umbra-panic · scrub <file>

   Press q to close this help.
EOF
read -n 1 -s -r
